<p>		   (IN THOUSANDS, EXCEPT PER SHARE DATA)</p>
<p>NOTE:  Shorewood Packaging Corp said it restated its results for 1996 to reflect operations of transportation division as &quot;discontinued.&quot;</p>
<p>The company said the extraordinary charges related to the early retirement of debt net of tax benefits.</p>
<p>Weighted average shares outstanding for 1997 decreased from 19,440,000 to 18,713,000 primarily as a result of the company's share repurchase programs.</p>
<p>Net results for fiscal 1997 include the operating losses, net of tax, of the transportation division which was discontinued (and since sold) during the fourth quarter, as well as an after-tax loss of $488,000 recorded during the fourth quarter on disposal of the related assets.</p>
<p>Net results for fiscal 1997 and 1996 also include an after-tax extraordinary charge related to the early retirement of debt which was refinanced in December 1995, and April 1997.</p>
